JAPAN
Japan is a land of contrasts. It can display the most neon-lit,
skyscrapered and expressway-lined face, yet find its inspiration in the
quiet beauty of the graceful Tori Gate and Mt. Fuji, pictured here. The
Japanese can run their trains at lightning speed, yet spend hours on
a small conversational courtesy. Here you will find graceful perfection
and formality contrasted with vigorous commerce. Pan Am serves
Tokyo on its Round-the-World flights and nonstop daily from New York,
San Francisco, Los Angeles, Honolulu, and Hong Kong. Osaka is
served nonstop from Honolulu.
